09/21/82  read_mail request: all

Syntax:  all {-control_args}


Syntax as an active request:  [all {-control_arg}]


Function:  prints the message numbers for all messages of the specified
type; as an active request, returns the message numbers separated by
spaces.


Control arguments:
-include_deleted, -idl
   prints or returns the message numbers of all messages in the mailbox
   whether or not they have been deleted.
-only_deleted, -odl
   prints or returns only the message numbers of those messages which
   have been deleted.
-only_non_deleted, -ondl
   prints or returns only the message numbers of those messages which
   have not been deleted.  (Default)
-reverse, -rv
   prints or returns the message numbers in reverse order.
-no_reverse, -nrv
   prints or returns the messages numbers in normal order (smaller
   numbers first).  (Default)


Notes:
If there are no messages of the indicated class, the active request
will return a null string.
